1- npm init -y : initialize node.js
2- npm i express ejs express-ejs-layouts : install packages required for the project
3- npm i --save-dev nodemon : refresh and restart server when saving files

Json - scripts
4- "start": "node server.js" - start server on production environment
command: 

5- "devStart": "nodemon server.js" - refresh and restart server after save
command: npm run devStart


6- npm i mongoose : install mongoose for mongodb
7- npm i --save-dev dotenv : access to local environment

not connectinting to env
//require('dotenv').config({ path: require('find-config')('.env') })
command: npm i find-config : finding .env

8- git init : initialise the git
9- git add . : adding all the files
10- git commit -m "Description"

